<item>
            <title>[FLINK-7483] BlobCache cleanup timer not reset after job re-registration</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-7483</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Since &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-7057&quot; title=&quot;move BLOB ref-counting from LibraryCacheManager to BlobCache&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-7057&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-7057&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, the blob cache handles cleanup via &lt;tt&gt;registerJob&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;releaseJob&lt;/tt&gt; calls where the latter sets a cleanup interval. &lt;tt&gt;registerJob&lt;/tt&gt;, however, forgets to reset this if the job is re-registered again and so the job&apos;s blobs will be cleaned up although it is still used!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13096393">FLINK-7483</key>
            <summary>BlobCache cleanup timer not reset after job re-registration</summary>
